<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-07-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-07-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="643" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d643">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to the
                                    <persName type="to">Duke de Arcos</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-07-28"><hi rend="italic">July 28,
                                1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Minister</hi>: A dispatch just received
                            from General Otis informs us that the Spanish agents in Manila have been
                            given full liberty to negotiate with the insurgents for the exchange of
                            prisoners.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>